Marius Oosthuizen is a business expert and he spoke to eNCA to unpack this. #Dstv403 JOHANNESBURG - One business expert believes the uncertainty in some of South Africa's policies, is preventing the private sector from investing. Earlier in the week, Stats SA announced that the economy declined 3.2 percent in the first quarter of the year. READ: Moody's warns of SA recession Economists have described it as the biggest quarterly contraction in a decade. According to Business expert, Marius Oosthuizen from the Gordon Institute of Business Science the reality is that SA is in the 10th year of the stagnation. "On the back on policy uncertainty and mismanagement on the economy, we are going to continue seeing the lack of growth unless we have a rapid investment in the economy." Watch the full interview above